Below is one way to “read off” the two structures from the images and match them (without rotations) to the dictionary blocks:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  There are TWO separate assemblies:

  A) The Red “Ring” on the Left  
     – Composed of two red half‐cylinders stacked to form a circular hole.
     – Visually, you can see a horizontal seam halfway up, meaning the top and bottom halves are each a “C”‐shaped red block.

  B) The “House” on the Right  
     – Built in four vertical layers (bottom to top).  
     – From the coloring and shape, a likely breakdown is:  
       • Layer 1 (bottom): Three green cubes side by side.  
       • Layer 2: Three orange cubes side by side (directly on top of the green row).  
       • Layer 3: Blue–Yellow–Blue cubes side by side, forming the top “walls” with a yellow center “window.”  
       • Layer 4 (roof): Two orange triangular blocks meeting in the middle to form a peaked roof.

•  Overall Block Count:
  – Ring = 2 blocks  
  – House = 11 blocks (3 green + 3 orange + 2 blue + 1 yellow + 2 orange triangles)  
  – Total = 13 blocks

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING MATCHING BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

A) Red Ring (2 blocks)  
   – Requires two red “C”‐shaped halves, oriented exactly as shown so that when stacked they form a circular hole.  
   – From the dictionary, #3 and #4 are the two complementary halves (one open to the left, the other open to the right).  
     • Bottom half: #3  
     • Top half:   #4  

B) House (11 blocks)
   1. Green Cubes (3×)  
      – Use green‐cube #6 three times (all cubes are identical aside from orientation; #6 is already upright).  
   2. Orange Cubes (3×)  
      – Use orange‐cube #7 three times for the second‐layer “walls.”  
   3. Blue Cubes (2×)  
      – Use blue‐cube #5 twice for the left‐ and right‐side cubes in the third layer.  
   4. Yellow Cube (1×)  
      – Use yellow‐cube #9 in the center of the third layer.  
   5. Orange Triangular Roof (2×)  
      – Use #15 and #16, which are orange wedge blocks oriented so that they form a symmetrical peak when placed side by side.

Hence the exact block indices needed are:
• #3, #4 (red halves for the ring)  
• #5 (blue cubes) – used twice  
• #6 (green cubes) – used three times  
• #7 (orange cubes) – used three times  
• #9 (yellow cube) – used once  
• #15, #16 (roof wedges) – used once each  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A possible build sequence (placing the ring first, then the house from bottom to top) is:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 3        // Bottom half of red ring
  Step2:  Move block with index 4        // Top half of red ring

  Step3:  Move block with index 6        // Bottom row of house (first green)
  Step4:  Move block with index 6        // Bottom row of house (second green)
  Step5:  Move block with index 6        // Bottom row of house (third green)

  Step6:  Move block with index 7        // Second layer of house (first orange)
  Step7:  Move block with index 7        // Second layer of house (second orange)
  Step8:  Move block with index 7        // Second layer of house (third orange)

  Step9:  Move block with index 5        // Third layer left (blue)
  Step10: Move block with index 9        // Third layer center (yellow)
  Step11: Move block with index 5        // Third layer right (blue)

  Step12: Move block with index 15       // Roof left
  Step13: Move block with index 16       // Roof right
}

That completes both the red ring on the left and the multi‐layered “house” on the right, exactly matching the target image using the blocks as‐is from the dictionary.
